XML (eXtensible Markup Language)
XML is a markup language designed to store and transport data in a human-readable format. It uses tags to define elements and hierarchically organize information. XML is widely used for configuration files, data exchange between systems, and storing structured data.

Example XML:

CopyRun
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<library>
  <book>
    <title>The Great Gatsby</title>
    <author>F. Scott Fitzgerald</author>
    <year>1925</year>
  </book>
  <book>
    <title>To Kill a Mockingbird</title>
    <author>Harper Lee</author>
    <year>1960</year>
  </book>
</library>
